{"md": "!tit two balls in a narrow box\n!descr Two heavy balls (each in a compartiment) in a 2D box interact with 300 small light balls.\n\n# Abstract\n\nWe study the friction question with two balls in a thin box with numerous small balls which regularily schock them. \n\n# Introduction \n\nWe want to test the model of friction with the force proportionnal to the velocity which is supposed to emerge from the random schocks in a gas. \n\n# Results \n\nAn exponential decrease for the velocities is observed for both balls as expected. Contrarily with the simulation with 300 balls, here using 1300 balls permits to avoid the transfer of vertical momentum to all the small balls. The two heavy balls see their velocity to converge toward a thermalisation level. \n\n[[fig:2||v|(t) \u2014 t = 1110.9 u.a.]]\n\n# Comments \n\nAt the end the small balls do not vibrate vertically as precedently. The two big balls have transmited all their energy to the small ones but mostly in the z direction. Their are still two modes in the histogram of the speeds.\n\n[[fig:1|histogramme des vitesses \u2014 t = 0.0 u.a.]]\n ", "figs": {"1": {"kind": "vhist", "url": "data:image/png;base64,"}, "2": {"kind": "v", "url": "data:image/png;base64,"}}, "seq": 2, "descr": "Two heavy balls (each in a compartiment) in a 2D box interact with 300 small light balls."}